result.execSummary:
The defendant Suzanne Y Geiger was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Suzanne Y Geiger in court, in custody, with attorney Samuel W. Benedict.  John Woodson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State makes sentencing recommendations.  Defense makes sentencing recommendations.  Mary Murphy, Probation & Parole Agent, makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the defendant as follows: 

WITHHELD SENTENCE;

TERM OF PROBATION: 2 1/2 YEARS; (Credit time 75-days, if revoked)

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.
*Attend self help groups
*Perform 40 hours of community service

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation); (Apply Cash Bail)
DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation); (Apply Cash Bail)
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
Apply Cash bail in the amount of $500.00, leaving a balance of $18.00.
The remaining cash bail is to be refunded to the poster.

CONDITION TIME: 90 days HUBER (standard work release conditions, including work and AODA), the last 46 days are STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
Character Letter from Cindy G., received 2/9/18.
